com.avaya.ic.sdk
Interface Channel

All Known Subinterfaces:
ChatChannel, EmailChannel, VoiceChannel
public interface Channel

The Channel interface is a generic representation of a delivery channel in IC. You can use a Channel to deliver MediaInteractions or Documents to a user.

getDeliveryStatus

Channel.DeliveryStatus getDeliveryStatus()
Get The delivery status for the channel. Indicates whether the channel is ready to receive new media interaction assignments. Used by the channel connection to report if Media Interactions or Documents can be delivered. This event is directly linked to the channel workload count (endpoints).

Returns:
The delivery status for the channel. Indicates whether the channel is ready to receive new media interaction assignments. Used by the channel connection to report if Media Interactions or Documents can be delivered. This event is directly linked to the channel workload count (endpoints).
